<?xml version="1.0"?>

<!-- 
EC NAVD flightplan

Author: litzi

This instrument is part of a 2D-panel simulating a NAVD found in EC series
helicopters. This instrument is called from the central EUcopter-navd-panel.xml file with a xml include statement.

This instruments shows the navigation display in plan mode without the compass rose. It is able to display 
up to 10 navaid symbols of which are up to 4 waypoints of the current flightplan. The symbols data are
driven by the navdisplay() function in the file mfd.nas .
 
Some components of this instrument are based on code and bitmaps of Syd Adams' Primus-1000 instrument.

-->

